success.question_category_path: General Ability / Non-Verbal Reasoning / Reasoning

review_1.column_1_text: Solution

review_3.column_1_text:
Each row has arrows pointing in the same direction.

One of the three circles is black.

The position of the black circle corresponds to the part of the arrow that is black (as the top circle is black and the ‘top’ of the arrow is also black).

Tip

The matrix consists of nine squares containing shapes which form a pattern. Look along a row, or down a column, to see how each tile is related to the next and use this relationship to find the shapes in the missing tile.

success.question_text:
Which two of the following statements together prove that:

SOME GIRLS PLAY CRICKET?

I. Sally and Marcia are girls.

II. Marcia and John are the same age.

III. Sally’s team sometimes plays against John’s team.

IV. John is the captain of his cricket team.

V. Sally is a better player than Marcia.
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Logic

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

(III and IV) Sally’s team sometimes plays against John’s team. John is the captain of his cricket team.
